detail.title: Upgrade core v1.5.0
detail.description:
Software Upgrade to v1.5.0.

This proposal is required to adopt version 1.5.0 which contains the Cosmos SDK v0.47.3 upgrade alongside many Millions and DFract protocol upgrades and improvements.

It is scheduled for block #8424000 which should land on Monday, July 17th around 15:15 UTC.
A more precise upgrade time will be provided over time as we move closer to the upgrade height.

All node operators must follow the upgrade procedure as usual.
The procedure alongside the git tag will be available at the following address:
https://github.com/lum-network/mainnet/blob/master/upgrades/v1.5.0/guide.md

Changelog:
- Upgrade to Cosmos SDK v0.47.3
  - Upgrade to Cosmos SDK v0.47
  - Migration to CometBFT
  - Upgrade to Ibc-go v7
  - Protobuf clean up and re-generation
- Millions - Handle pool paused state
  - Properly handle all pool states (especially Paused state to prevent Draws from happening)
  - Pool state update via governance proposal
- Millions - Allow native zone toAddress
  - Allow for withdrawals to go directly on a remote zone wallet (instead of going back to the Lum Network)
- Millions - Handle re-delegate assets from a disabled validator
  - Evenly redelegate assets from disabled validators (not part of the active set anymore) upon Pool update proposal success
- Millions - Add msg to edit a deposit
  - Edit winner address
  - Edit sponsor mode
- Millions - Fix draw prizes fees implementation
  - Migration to add uncollected fees to the PrizePool not included in this fixe, this should be evaluated at a later time due to the low amount which has not been collected
- Millions - Prize uniqueness capability for Prize batches
  - Allow for a Prize batch to be consider a 'unique win' to prevent a winner to win other prizes
- DFract - move from Proposal to Tx based minting
  - Change WithdrawAndMint proposal into an UpdateParams proposal with an UpdateParams handler
  - Add a new tx based message WithdrawAndMint
- ATOM Pool prize strategy update
  - Make the biggest prize a 'unique' win to prevent the winner (in case a winner is found) to also win other prizes
  - Slight review of prize batches in order to better distribute the winning chances and the amounts according to the current prize pool

Additional information:
- Upgrade pull request: https://github.com/lum-network/chain/pull/38
- ATOM Pool prize strategy update: https://github.com/lum-network/chain/commit/d09395209a3dae9474c51883ea9b856115c1a054

detail.title: DFract Allocation #40
detail.description:
DFract Allocation #40

Governance proposal for the DFract protocol on the Lum Network (dfract.fi).

This proposal is required in order to use the funds available in the DFract module account (at the time the proposal passes) in order to buy the designated assets on Osmosis and delegate them on their native blockchain.

The list of assets alongside the repartition of the funds is available on the official DFract website (dfract.fi).

This proposal will set the new DFR mint rate to 1.578924 since the protocol treasury underlying value changed by about -0.89% since the previous proposal.

Stakers must:
- Vote YES to use the funds from the DFract module account vault and increase DFract protocol value
- Vote NO to reject this proposal and let the funds in the DFract module account vault

detail.description:
# [Cosmos Millions] ATOM Pool Launch

## Description
This proposal introduces the first Cosmos Millions Pool: **ATOM**
This proposal is similar to proposal #65 since the Pool from this proposal was never actived due to a chain halt.

The ATOM pool will be bootstrapped with a minimum of $100,000, courtesy of the [ATOM Accelerator DAO](https://www.atomaccelerator.com/) grant program.
The grant will be added to the Pool as soon as its setup is completed and the Pool is available on Cosmos Millions' web application.

This proposal introduces the following initial configuration for the Pool:
- Minimum deposit: 0.5 ATOM
- Draw every Tuesday at noon UTC (12:00)
  - Starting on June 20th, 2023
- Prizes
  - 1 prize | 20% chance to win | 40% of the Prize Pool
  - 20 prizes | 20% chance to win each prize | 10% of the Prize Pool
  - 100 prizes | 20% chance to win each prize | 20% of the Prize Pool
  - 300 prizes | 20% chance to win each prize | 30% of the Prize Pool

As per the Cosmos Millions protocol specifications, this configuration is not set in stone and shall be revised and updated via governance proposals in accordance to community discussions and decisions.

Additional information:
- Upgrade pull request: https://github.com/lum-network/chain/pull/24

detail.title: Upgrade core v1.3.1
detail.description:
Software Upgrade to v1.3.1
This proposal is required to adopt version 1.3.1 which fixes the pruning and DFract module issues introduced in v1.3.0.

Current pruning issue is due to a badly initialized module (IBCFee required for later DFract version).
We unregister it in the v1.3.1 and add it for registering on a future v1.3.2 upgrade.

Current DFract issue is due to the allowed denoms param being changed from string to array of strings, not migrated properly.
The upgrade correctly apply the default params to the store and fix the DFract module processing logic.

It is scheduled for block 5890500 which should land on Wednesday, January 25th around 16:00 UTC.

All node operators must follow the upgrade procedure detailed on Github: https://github.com/lum-network/mainnet/blob/master/upgrades/v1.3.1/guide.md

PR: https://github.com/lum-network/chain/pull/21

detail.title: Upgrade core v1.3.0
detail.description:
Software Upgrade to v1.3.0

This proposal is required to adopt version 1.3.0 which notably upgrade the Cosmos SDK to v0.46.6 and enforces the patch of the Dragonberry vulnerability.

Please note that due to its sensitive nature, the Dragonberry vulnerability has already been patched silently by a majority of validator nodes, rendering the exploit unusable.
This upgrade enforces the use by ALL validators of a version preventing the exploit of the Dragonberry vulnerability.

It is scheduled for block 5672000 which should land on Tuesday, January 10th around 16:00 UTC.

All node operators must follow the upgrade procedure detailed on Github: https://github.com/lum-network/mainnet/blob/master/upgrades/v1.3.0/guide.md

For more information regarding the Dragonberry vulnerability:
- https://github.com/cosmos/cosmos-sdk/releases/tag/v0.45.9
- https://forum.cosmos.network/t/ibc-security-advisory-dragonberry/7702

Associated PRs:
- https://github.com/lum-network/chain/pull/14
- https://github.com/lum-network/chain/pull/18
- https://github.com/lum-network/chain/pull/19

List of changes (full list available on Github in the upgrade guide):
- Upgrade to Cosmos SDK v0.46.6
- Dragonberry permanent patch
- Switch the keyring backend from test to file

detail.title: Upgrade core v1.0.5
detail.description:
Software Upgrade to v1.0.5

This proposal is required to adopt version 1.0.5.
All node operators must follow the upgrade procedure detailed in the PR.

This upgrade introduces fixes and improvements to the IBC integration, notably regarding the Osmosis-Lum connection.

It is scheduled for block 90300 which should land on Dec. 20 around 17:00 UTC.

PR: https://github.com/lum-network/chain/pull/6


Details:

The main-net of the Lum Network was launched on Dec. 14th. The same day Osmosis ran an update as well which broke the capability to create IBC channels between Osmosis and Lum Network. Thus preventing us from creating liquidity pools on the Osmosis platform.

This upgrade to v1.0.5 alongside Osmosis upgrade (which will happen the same day) is intended to fix this IBC integration issue and enable our networks to communicate.
